Name: autoimmune disease of skin and connective tissue
Definition: An autoimmune hypersensitivity disease that is the abnormal functioning of the immune system that causes your immune system to produce antibodies or T cells against cells and/or tissues in the skin and connective tissue.

Name: yaws
Definition: A primary bacterial infectious disease that results in infection located in skin

Name: Ludwig's angina
Definition: An ovarian carcinoma that is characterized by large pleiomorphic cells with large round or oval nuclei

Name: bullous skin disease
Definition: An autoimmune disease of skin and connective tissue that is characterized by blisters filled with a watery fluid
